Kenya's deputy environment minister, Maathai, aims to reduce plastic bag usage due to the risk of malaria from discarded bags.
The UN Environment Programme supports banning plastic bags in Kenya.
In Eritrea, a law replaced plastic bags with cotton and nylon, leading to cleaner streets.
San Francisco and other cities propose fees on grocery bags to reduce waste.
Rwanda and Uganda are enforcing bans on plastic bags to protect the environment.
Tanzania is establishing a recycling plant to address plastic waste.
These efforts reflect a growing global movement towards reducing plastic pollution and promoting sustainable practices.
